## Attribution and Acknowledgments

This project builds upon and is inspired by the following works:

### Primary Research Inspiration
**"Graph Analysis for Detecting Fraud, Waste, and Abuse in Healthcare Data"**
- Authors: Juan Liu, Eric Bier, Aaron Wilson, Tomo Honda, Sricharan Kumar, Leilani Gilpin, John Guerra-Gomez, and Daniel Davies
- Institution: Palo Alto Research Center (PARC)
- Publication: AI Magazine, AAAI
- URL: https://ojs.aaai.org/aimagazine/index.php/aimagazine/article/view/2630/2554
- Note: Graph-based fraud detection methodology and network analysis techniques adapted from this research

### Data Generation Tools
**Syntheaâ„¢ Patient Generator**
- Project: Synthea - Synthetic Patient Population Simulator
- Repository: https://github.com/synthetichealth/synthea
- License: Apache License 2.0
- Usage: All synthetic healthcare data in this project generated using Synthea

**Synthea International**
- Project: International configurations for Synthea
- Repository: https://github.com/synthetichealth/synthea-international
- License: Apache License 2.0
- Usage: Ireland-specific healthcare configurations (IE module)

### Educational Context
- **Institution:** UCD Professional Academy
- **Program:** Data Analytics: Machine Learning Certificate (Batch: 25/09/2025)
- **Lecturer:** Sajal Minhas
- **Purpose:** Capstone project for ML certificate program

